INSERT INTO test_questions (testId, moduleId, questionText, questionType, options, correctAnswer, explanation, points, difficulty, isActive) VALUES
-- Module 2: Understanding the EU AI Act (need 41 more)
(1, 2, 'What is the EU AI Act primary classification system based on?', 'multiple_choice', '["A) Cost", "B) Risk levels", "C) Company size", "D) Country of origin"]', 'B', 'The EU AI Act uses a risk-based approach, classifying AI systems as unacceptable, high, limited, or minimal risk.', 1, 'easy', 1),
(1, 2, 'Which AI practice is explicitly prohibited under the EU AI Act?', 'multiple_choice', '["A) Chatbots", "B) Social scoring by governments", "C) Recommendation systems", "D) Translation tools"]', 'B', 'Social scoring by public authorities is explicitly prohibited as an unacceptable risk AI practice.', 1, 'easy', 1),
(1, 2, 'What is a "high-risk" AI system under the EU AI Act?', 'multiple_choice', '["A) Expensive systems", "B) Systems posing significant risks to safety or fundamental rights", "C) Complex algorithms", "D) Popular applications"]', 'B', 'High-risk AI systems are those that pose significant risks to health, safety, or fundamental rights.', 1, 'medium', 1),
(1, 2, 'What must providers of high-risk AI systems establish?', 'multiple_choice', '["A) Minimum prices", "B) Quality management systems", "C) Marketing departments", "D) Physical offices in EU"]', 'B', 'Providers must establish and maintain quality management systems for high-risk AI.', 1, 'medium', 1),
(1, 2, 'What is required for general-purpose AI models?', 'multiple_choice', '["A) No requirements", "B) Transparency obligations and technical documentation", "C) Complete ban", "D) Government approval"]', 'B', 'General-purpose AI models must meet transparency obligations and maintain technical documentation.', 1, 'hard', 1)
